 witnesses form a right-cloven family over their underlying sections (). In particular, an isomorphism of sections of r from 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen s,h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 to 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen s',h'\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 is given by a homotopy H_s \colon  s \sim  s' together with a higher homotopy H_h \colon  h \sim    \mathopen {}\left \lparen \lambda {x}\mathpunct {.}\mathsf {act}_{r}  \mathopen {}\left \lparen H_s x\right \rparen \mathclose {} \cdot  h'x\right \rparen \mathclose {} .

